item.title: Payment Instructions
item.dc:creator: chess-rso
item.content:encoded:
1. Navigate here to access the payment platform.
  2. Check the box "This payment is NOT a donation".
  3. For "What fundraiser is this for?", click on Other.
  4. In the Comment option write your name followed by Tournament Payment (ex. Aryan Joshi Tournament Payment).
  5. Enter your total tournament fee.
    • Open section:
      • All GMs, IMs, WGMs: Free entry, $100 deducted from prize
      • FMs, WIMs, WFMs, NMs: $100 entry (reduced fee) by January 27th, $110 later online or at site.
      • Everyone else: $130 entry fee, $140 on-site. If the published rating is under 1900 at the time of registration, then an additional $75 play-up fee applies. Unrated ineligible to enter.
      • U1900 section:
        • U1900: $90 by January 27th, $100 later online or at site.
      • U1400 section:
        • $45 online by January 30th, 4:00 pm. $55 on-site. $10 less for unrated players.
  6. Click on Add to Cart.
  7. Click on shopping cart at top right of your screen.
  8. Check the Terms of Service checkbox.
  9. Click the Checkout button.
  10. Click "Checkout as Guest".
  11. Fill out Phone Number and enter the confirmation code.
  12. Add your billing address, email, card details and proceed to pay.
  13. Attach a screenshot of payment confirmation. like the one shown below to the tournament signup form.

item.title: Open Section
item.dc:creator: vinamrajain
item.content:encoded:
OVERVIEW

The UMass Winter Classic will be held from January 31 to February 1st, 2026. This is a 5-round US Chess-rated event with a $5,000 prize fund for the open section ($10,000 total prize fund for the whole event). It will be hosted in the Student Union Ballroom at 41 Campus Center Way, Amherst, MA 01002. Please bring your own sets and chess clocks.

TIME CONTROL & ROUND TIMES

G/90;d5.

Saturday: 10 am, 2:30 pm, 6 pm

Sunday: 10 am, 2:30 pm

PRIZES 

$2000 - $1250 - $750

Top U2300: $600

Top U2100: $400

Please note that the prizes above are based on 50 players. 

ENTRY FEE 

All GMs, IMs, WGMs: Free entry, $100 deducted from prize

FMs, WIMs, WFMs, NMs: $100 entry (reduced fee) by January 27th, $110 later online or at site.

Everyone else: $130 entry fee, $140 on-site. If the published rating is under 1900 at the time of registration, then an additional $75 play-up fee applies. Unrated ineligible to enter.

REGISTRATION

  • Online registration is strongly recommended
  • Online registration closes January 30th, 4:00 pm
  • On-Site Registration closes January 31st, 9:00 am.
  • For on-site registration, please bring exact change

PARKING

Vehicles may park in any available non-restricted, non-reserved space or lot for free (no parking permit required). These are the red lots in this map. The closest of these lots to the Student Union (event venue) are lots 64, 30, 63. The closest parking to the Student Union is the paid parking in the Campus Center garage ($1.85/hr).

*Payment Disclaimer* In order to receive your winnings, you must register yourself as a vendor with the University of Massachusetts Amherst. We will provide the link to the vendor site once the winners are confirmed. Once filled out, the University of Massachusetts Amherst will pay your winnings, however, it may take longer than 3-4 weeks. This is the only way the University of Massachusetts Amherst Chess Club can pay your winnings.

item.title: Blitz
item.dc:creator: vinamrajain
item.content:encoded:
OVERVIEW

The UMass Winter Blitz will be held on February 1st, 2026, at 6 pm. It is a ten-round, double-round robin USCF-rated tournament. It will be hosted in the Student Union Ballroom at 41 Campus Center Way, Amherst, MA 01002. Please bring your own sets and chess clocks.

TIME CONTROL: 3+2

FORMAT 

Players, based on their strength, will be divided into groups of six players. From there, you play 2 games with each opponent - one white and one black - getting to a total of 10 games. Between each set of 6 players, the first players win $80. In case of a tie, Armageddons with bids will be used to determine a winner. 

ENTRY FEE: $20, Navigate here to access the payment platform or pay by cash.

REGISTRATION

Closes at 5:30 PM or when the last game of the classical tournament ends. Please tell us as soon as you can if you want to play in the Blitz.

*Payment Disclaimer* In order to receive your winnings, you must register yourself as a vendor with the University of Massachusetts Amherst. We will provide the link to the vendor site once the winners are confirmed. Once filled out, the University of Massachusetts Amherst will pay your winnings, however, it may take longer than 3-4 weeks. This is the only way the University of Massachusetts Amherst Chess Club can pay your winnings.

item.content:encoded:
Welcome to the UMass Amherst Chess Club Website!

We play chess!

Tournament Registration!

Taken from the 2nd UMass Spring Classic

Our Club

The UMass club is your stop for any chess endeavors! We provide a social network in person and online through which you can meet players of your skill level to practice and improve together. We meet Mondays and Thursdays from 6:00PM to 9:00PM at the Blue Wall(located inside Campus Center) for casual games.

Players of all skill levels welcome (including beginners/people who don't know how to play)! Open to both UMass students and non-students alike.

We also host an annual classical USCF rated tournament, the UMass Spring Classic, which attracts over 150 players from around the Northeast.

"We promote chess like David promotes pawns"
